reut2-006.sgm, TREASURY'S BAKER CALLS FOR NEW BRAZIL PLAN, Treasury Secretary James Baker saidthat Brazil should come up with a new economic plan if it hopesto get additional assistance from commercial banks and others.    In testimony before a House appropriations subcommittee,Baker said that he had given that message to Brazilianofficials earlier this month when they met for talks inWashington.    He said that the so-called Cruzado Plan had worked for awhile, but that new efforts by the government are now required.    Baker made it clear that he backed the decision by theParis Club official creditors to reschedule loans to Brazil,even though the country later froze its payments to commercialbank creditors.    He said that the official loans are being serviced and thatthis was a result of the rescheduling. Reuter&#3;
