reut2-006.sgm, ONE DEAD AS PHILIPPINE ARMY SCHOOL BOMBED, A bomb blast at the Philippine MilitaryAcademy killed at least one person and wounded about 40 duringrehearsals for a weekend visit by President Corazon Aquino,military and hospital officials said.    Reporters at the scene told Reuters the death toll waslikely to rise, but there was no official confirmation.    Military sources at first suggested the bomb might havebeen planted by communist rebels, but no group immediatelyclaimed responsibility. REUTER&#3;
